1
00:00:11,510 --> 00:00:13,390
It has been a few months since I came

2
00:00:12,710 --> 00:00:15,250
[Year 1901]

3
00:00:13,640 --> 00:00:16,100
to China from Italy to study the Grand Canal.

4
00:00:16,390 --> 00:00:17,230
Today,

5
00:00:17,230 --> 00:00:20,950
as I was lifted into the air in a hanging basket

6
00:00:21,190 --> 00:00:22,750
before the gates of Wuxi,

7
00:00:22,750 --> 00:00:24,320
I felt for the first time what it was like

8
00:00:24,320 --> 00:00:27,670
to rise above the world of smoke and fire.

9
00:00:28,110 --> 00:00:29,110
It's also here that

10
00:00:29,110 --> 00:00:30,780
I met my Chinese translator,

11
00:00:30,780 --> 00:00:32,030
Xie Pingyao.

12
00:00:32,189 --> 00:00:34,940
He will go northward with me

13
00:00:34,950 --> 00:00:37,870
and start our journey on the canal.

14
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:44,550
You, the one wearing the red hat!

15
00:00:44,610 --> 00:00:45,930
Add five cents more!

16
00:00:45,950 --> 00:00:48,910
Pull me up! I'm stuck!

17
00:00:50,910 --> 00:00:53,960
Who let them stop? Wait!

18
00:00:54,380 --> 00:00:55,800
They want more money.

19
00:00:55,860 --> 00:00:58,440
Otherwise, they won't pull you up.

20
00:01:22,310 --> 00:01:24,039
This thousand-year-old canal

21
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:26,310
carries the enduring history and cultural legacy

22
00:01:26,310 --> 00:01:28,190
of the Chinese civilization.

23
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:30,700
It has nurtured and enriched

24
00:01:30,730 --> 00:01:33,660
the lives of countless families living by the canal.

25
00:01:34,460 --> 00:01:36,740
Ships traveling north and south

26
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:39,229
carry memories that span across the ages.

27
00:01:39,390 --> 00:01:42,020
For people living by the canal,

28
00:01:42,670 --> 00:01:45,070
the canal is more than just a waterway.

29
00:01:45,100 --> 00:01:46,770
It's also a compass,

30
00:01:46,789 --> 00:01:49,110
pointing the way to the world.

31
00:01:49,539 --> 00:01:53,509
The canal is their vanguard in discovering the world.

32
00:01:54,229 --> 00:01:55,900
It stands for them,

33
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,240
and journeys in their place

34
00:01:57,240 --> 00:02:00,080
to a wider and more expansive world.

35
00:02:01,120 --> 00:02:04,840
The canal even signifies

36
00:02:04,850 --> 00:02:06,610
their entire lives.

37
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:47,400
[NORTHWARD]

38
00:03:47,540 --> 00:03:49,310
[Episode 1]

39
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:53,340
[Year 2000]

40
00:03:54,329 --> 00:03:55,829
In the year 2000,

41
00:03:56,190 --> 00:03:58,600
as the new millennium arrived,

42
00:03:58,890 --> 00:04:00,770
the children living by the canal

43
00:04:00,790 --> 00:04:04,330
may still struggle to discern between the directions.

44
00:04:04,380 --> 00:04:06,630
However, they had already begun to know that

45
00:04:06,630 --> 00:04:08,710
if one heads left at the end of the bridge,

46
00:04:08,710 --> 00:04:11,010
it leads to the Forbidden City, the Great Wall,

47
00:04:11,010 --> 00:04:12,790
and Quanjude roast duck.

48
00:04:13,170 --> 00:04:14,160
If one heads right,

49
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:17,160
it leads to the dazzling neon lights of Nanjing Road

50
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:19,399
and White Rabbit candy.

51
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:20,500
If one heads down,

52
00:04:20,529 --> 00:04:24,900
there will be an endless supply of free watermelon.

53
00:04:30,150 --> 00:04:31,910
The ship is here!

54
00:04:35,350 --> 00:04:36,960
Hurry! Run!

55
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,190
Hurry up!

56
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:39,270
Haikuo, get ready.

57
00:04:39,270 --> 00:04:40,040
Okay!

58
00:04:43,230 --> 00:04:44,060
Hurry, run!

59
00:04:44,060 --> 00:04:44,990
I know, I know.

60
00:04:44,990 --> 00:04:46,150
Xie Wanghe, hurry up!

61
00:04:46,150 --> 00:04:46,790
Got it.

62
00:04:46,790 --> 00:04:48,150
Shao Xingchi, you're the slowest.

63
00:04:48,150 --> 00:04:48,790
Come on, hurry!

64
00:04:48,790 --> 00:04:49,270
Wait for me.

65
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:50,730
The ship is here, hurry up.

66
00:04:50,790 --> 00:04:52,790
-Xie Wanghe!
-Hurry up!

67
00:04:53,020 --> 00:04:53,950
Hurry up!

68
00:04:53,950 --> 00:04:55,010
Xingchi, hurry up.

69
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:57,850
Shao Xingchi, hurry up!

70
00:04:57,950 --> 00:04:58,830
Hurry!

71
00:04:58,830 --> 00:04:59,590
The ship is here.

72
00:04:59,590 --> 00:05:00,360
Hurry up.

73
00:05:00,510 --> 00:05:01,350
Hurry, hurry!

74
00:05:01,350 --> 00:05:02,120
Stop nagging.

75
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,120
Go watch the ship.

76
00:05:09,670 --> 00:05:10,810
Get ready!

77
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:25,180
Jump!

78
00:05:48,110 --> 00:05:49,390
Run!

79
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:50,620
Run!

80
00:05:50,620 --> 00:05:51,630
You brats!

81
00:05:51,860 --> 00:05:52,870
Do you want to die?

82
00:05:53,030 --> 00:05:54,430
Put down my watermelons!

83
00:05:54,470 --> 00:05:56,050
Xingchi, run!

84
00:05:56,950 --> 00:05:58,170
Run! Quick!

85
00:05:59,159 --> 00:06:00,460
My watermelons!

86
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:02,750
Don't you jump!

87
00:06:02,950 --> 00:06:04,250
Do you want to die?

88
00:06:15,270 --> 00:06:16,550
I know you!

89
00:06:16,670 --> 00:06:18,310
You're Boss Xie's son!

90
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:19,410
Later,

91
00:06:19,650 --> 00:06:22,910
I'll tell your dad to punish you!

92
00:06:23,580 --> 00:06:25,580
If you dare to steal my watermelons,

93
00:06:27,510 --> 00:06:30,540
I'll make sure to skin you alive!

94
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,600
My name is Fenghua.

95
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:34,190
This is the 10-year-old me.

96
00:06:34,250 --> 00:06:37,030
As you can see, my baby teeth have yet to fully fall out.

97
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,430
The ones running ahead

98
00:06:38,460 --> 00:06:40,330
are my neighbors,

99
00:06:40,370 --> 00:06:44,510
Xie Wanghe, Shao Xingchi, and Zhou Haikuo.

100
00:06:44,530 --> 00:06:47,190
We all live on Flower Street.

101
00:06:47,710 --> 00:06:49,030
At that time,

102
00:06:49,050 --> 00:06:50,970
we were fooling around every day,

103
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:53,290
and our little gang was well-known.

104
00:06:53,370 --> 00:06:55,010
We were excellent swimmers

105
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,800
and notorious troublemakers.

106
00:06:56,850 --> 00:06:59,990
We were known for catching mussels and prawns, and stealing watermelons.

107
00:06:59,990 --> 00:07:01,070
Summer

108
00:07:01,090 --> 00:07:03,280
is our happiest time of the year.

109
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:06,680
As the saying goes, with protection comes ease of mind.

110
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:09,540
Under the protection of the canal and our families,

111
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:11,200
our childhood days

112
00:07:11,260 --> 00:07:12,730
were carefree.

113
00:07:12,780 --> 00:07:15,860
It was like a beautiful dream.

114
00:07:15,080 --> 00:07:20,270
[Flower Street]

115
00:07:28,190 --> 00:07:29,110
Haihong!

116
00:07:29,990 --> 00:07:30,980
Haihong!

117
00:07:31,380 --> 00:07:32,740
Liang Haihong!

118
00:07:33,550 --> 00:07:34,590
Yes, Mr. Zhang?

119
00:07:34,640 --> 00:07:35,730
Haihong!

120
00:07:35,950 --> 00:07:37,270
Let me tell you something!

121
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:37,920
What's wrong?

122
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:40,470
Your brat stole my watermelons.

123
00:07:41,150 --> 00:07:43,230
He stole more than a dozen of them.

124
00:07:43,230 --> 00:07:44,230
I'm telling you,

125
00:07:44,230 --> 00:07:46,520
your son must take responsibility for this.

126
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:47,310
Mr. Zhang.

127
00:07:47,310 --> 00:07:49,510
I understand. Please don't stay mad at the child.

128
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:50,680
As for the payment for the watermelons,

129
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:53,080
I'll bring it over with my eldest son later.

130
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:56,590
The first bow is to heaven and earth.

131
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:03,200
The second bow is to the parents.

132
00:08:04,670 --> 00:08:07,340
The couple bows to each other.

133
00:08:09,460 --> 00:08:12,140
The ceremony concludes.

134
00:08:18,680 --> 00:08:20,230
Hey, bride!

135
00:08:22,990 --> 00:08:24,590
The bride is so beautiful!

136
00:08:24,590 --> 00:08:26,750
When I grow up, I want to have my wedding on a ship too.

137
00:08:26,750 --> 00:08:28,910
You're talking as if you could even get married.

138
00:08:28,910 --> 00:08:29,930
If no one wants me,

139
00:08:29,930 --> 00:08:31,430
I'll marry Wanghe.

140
00:08:31,430 --> 00:08:32,309
I'll pass.

141
00:08:32,309 --> 00:08:33,350
You're a glutton.

142
00:08:33,350 --> 00:08:35,809
My family will go bankrupt from feeding you.

143
00:08:36,190 --> 00:08:37,250
What are you doing?

144
00:08:40,030 --> 00:08:40,830
Look.

145
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,870
That's the groom and the bride.

146
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:44,270
Isn't she pretty?

147
00:08:45,270 --> 00:08:46,320
Granny Ma!

148
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,270
Granny Ma!

149
00:08:47,350 --> 00:08:49,230
Wanghe!

150
00:08:49,230 --> 00:08:50,590
Fenghua!

151
00:08:50,590 --> 00:08:51,790
Granny Ma!

152
00:08:54,670 --> 00:08:55,820
Slow down.

153
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:58,070
Granny Ma!

154
00:08:58,070 --> 00:09:00,210
Look, they're here to greet you.

155
00:09:01,990 --> 00:09:04,610
Granny Ma.

156
00:09:04,630 --> 00:09:05,140
Granny Ma.

157
00:09:05,140 --> 00:09:06,550
Did you guys miss me?

158
00:09:06,590 --> 00:09:07,450
Granny Ma.

159
00:09:07,490 --> 00:09:08,090
Granny Ma.

160
00:09:08,220 --> 00:09:10,260
I've missed you too.

161
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:11,680
Who is she?

162
00:09:11,750 --> 00:09:13,150
She's my granddaughter.

163
00:09:13,530 --> 00:09:15,090
Are you a foreigner?

164
00:09:15,270 --> 00:09:16,620
No way.

165
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:18,160
Look at her face.

166
00:09:18,190 --> 00:09:19,450
Mixed-blood people look like this.

167
00:09:19,450 --> 00:09:21,250
I have seen some of them

168
00:09:21,280 --> 00:09:22,710
when they ate at my father's restaurant.

169
00:09:22,710 --> 00:09:23,500
Really?

170
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:24,750
My name is Fenghua.

171
00:09:24,750 --> 00:09:25,750
What's your name?

172
00:09:25,910 --> 00:09:27,330
Ma Siyi.

173
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,030
What?

174
00:09:28,070 --> 00:09:29,010
Louder, I can't hear you.

175
00:09:29,010 --> 00:09:30,960
Are you deaf? Her name is Ma Siyi.

176
00:09:31,610 --> 00:09:32,500
Okay.

177
00:09:32,940 --> 00:09:34,690
Hello, I'm Xie Wanghe.

178
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:35,570
This is Zhou Haikuo.

179
00:09:35,570 --> 00:09:36,500
This is Shao Xingchi.

180
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:38,230
-Hello. Hello.
-Hello. Hello.

181
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:39,630
You can play the guitar?

182
00:09:39,640 --> 00:09:40,730
A little.

183
00:09:40,870 --> 00:09:42,570
Play it for us.

184
00:09:42,650 --> 00:09:43,830
This is my dad's guitar.

185
00:09:43,830 --> 00:09:44,950
Why can't I touch it?

186
00:09:44,950 --> 00:09:46,950
Go away. Go away.

187
00:09:47,560 --> 00:09:48,950
Let's go back.

188
00:09:51,050 --> 00:09:52,070
She's a girl.

189
00:09:52,110 --> 00:09:53,310
Don't run so fast!

190
00:09:53,470 --> 00:09:55,470
Let me carry the guitar case for you.

191
00:09:58,910 --> 00:09:59,590
You naughty boy!

192
00:09:59,590 --> 00:10:01,130
All you know is to run wild all day long.

193
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:02,450
He's driving me crazy.

194
00:10:02,610 --> 00:10:03,930
Granny Ma is back.

195
00:10:03,980 --> 00:10:04,950
Granny Ma!

196
00:10:05,350 --> 00:10:06,070
This is...

197
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:07,150
Siyi?

198
00:10:07,150 --> 00:10:07,590
Siyi!

199
00:10:07,630 --> 00:10:08,790
Look at this kid.

200
00:10:08,790 --> 00:10:09,270
Look.

201
00:10:09,270 --> 00:10:10,200
You've grown up.

202
00:10:10,230 --> 00:10:11,380
Right?

203
00:10:11,750 --> 00:10:13,110
You've grown so tall.

204
00:10:13,350 --> 00:10:15,110
Siyi, look.

205
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:16,950
This is Aunt Liang,

206
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:19,470
Aunt Yan, and Aunt Ling.

207
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:21,210
Is she here for vacation?

208
00:10:22,780 --> 00:10:23,460
Yes.

209
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:25,720
She's staying here for a while.

210
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:27,030
Go on with your work.

211
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:27,550
I'm leaving.

212
00:10:27,550 --> 00:10:29,530
Siyi, say goodbye to your aunties.

213
00:10:29,710 --> 00:10:30,460
Bye.

214
00:10:30,510 --> 00:10:31,350
Bye, Siyi.

215
00:10:31,350 --> 00:10:32,270
Go on with your work.

216
00:10:32,270 --> 00:10:32,960
Alright.

217
00:10:33,070 --> 00:10:34,550
Go back and rest.

218
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:35,310
Don't worry about it.

219
00:10:35,310 --> 00:10:36,430
We're all here.

220
00:10:36,430 --> 00:10:37,950
Just tell us if you need anything.

221
00:10:37,950 --> 00:10:38,870
Okay.

222
00:10:38,870 --> 00:10:39,530
Be careful.

223
00:10:41,560 --> 00:10:42,680
Why did she bring

224
00:10:42,710 --> 00:10:44,400
the child back all of a sudden?

225
00:10:44,950 --> 00:10:47,160
She said the child would be staying for a while.

226
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:49,360
What about the kid's mother?

227
00:10:50,920 --> 00:10:52,920
Didn't her daughter-in-law remarry?

228
00:10:52,920 --> 00:10:54,330
She just had a son.

229
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:56,800
They must think

230
00:10:57,130 --> 00:10:58,460
the child's an eyesore.

231
00:11:00,450 --> 00:11:01,610
Slow down.

232
00:11:03,020 --> 00:11:04,900
They are quite mischievous.

233
00:11:04,920 --> 00:11:05,860
Siyi!

234
00:11:06,380 --> 00:11:07,320
Siyi.

235
00:11:07,580 --> 00:11:09,580
Siyi, come play with us.

236
00:11:09,580 --> 00:11:09,970
Yes.

237
00:11:09,990 --> 00:11:11,510
Let's go out and play.

238
00:11:11,540 --> 00:11:12,870
She's too tired today.

239
00:11:12,910 --> 00:11:14,390
She'll play with you tomorrow, okay?

240
00:11:14,390 --> 00:11:14,740
Okay.

241
00:11:14,830 --> 00:11:15,610
Okay.

242
00:11:15,630 --> 00:11:16,800
See you tomorrow.

243
00:11:16,830 --> 00:11:19,090
I'm making wontons for dinner, so come over and eat.

244
00:11:19,090 --> 00:11:19,940
Okay!

245
00:11:19,970 --> 00:11:21,100
Let's eat together.

246
00:11:25,550 --> 00:11:27,760
This is our home.

247
00:11:28,430 --> 00:11:29,760
Come in.

248
00:11:34,430 --> 00:11:35,360
Siyi.

249
00:11:36,530 --> 00:11:38,010
You must be tired today.

250
00:11:38,110 --> 00:11:39,950
I'll take you to school tomorrow

251
00:11:39,950 --> 00:11:41,150
for the procedures.

252
00:11:42,580 --> 00:11:45,050
Let me put your luggage in your room.

253
00:11:54,710 --> 00:11:57,500
It was a typical summer day when Siyi

254
00:11:57,530 --> 00:11:59,590
came to our Flower Street courtyard.

255
00:12:00,500 --> 00:12:02,450
In contrast to our cacophony,

256
00:12:02,800 --> 00:12:04,310
Siyi was quiet

257
00:12:04,350 --> 00:12:05,390
and headstrong.

258
00:12:05,460 --> 00:12:06,920
She also seemed troubled.

259
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:10,340
At that time, we had no idea that

260
00:12:10,830 --> 00:12:12,330
this foreign-looking girl

261
00:12:12,330 --> 00:12:13,860
who doesn't talk much

262
00:12:14,430 --> 00:12:16,580
will eventually change our life.

263
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:25,930
Want to see where you're sleeping?

264
00:12:25,970 --> 00:12:26,760
Come.

265
00:12:27,170 --> 00:12:27,890
Here.

266
00:12:29,830 --> 00:12:31,210
It's here.

267
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:34,370
You'll sleep here with me at night.

268
00:12:35,830 --> 00:12:37,270
Look at your guitar case.

269
00:12:37,270 --> 00:12:38,550
Shall we put it here?

270
00:12:38,560 --> 00:12:39,110
Here.

271
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,360
Yes, give it to me.

272
00:12:41,710 --> 00:12:42,620
Okay.

273
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:44,190
Grandma.

274
00:12:45,410 --> 00:12:47,850
Will I be staying here from now on?

275
00:12:49,170 --> 00:12:51,810
What did your mother tell you?

276
00:12:51,890 --> 00:12:53,810
She said you're old,

277
00:12:53,820 --> 00:12:55,950
so she asked me to help take care of you.

278
00:12:56,070 --> 00:12:57,390
Exactly.

279
00:12:57,420 --> 00:12:58,900
I'm getting old,

280
00:12:58,940 --> 00:13:00,200
so I need you to take care of me.

281
00:13:00,200 --> 00:13:01,200
Isn't it?

282
00:13:01,230 --> 00:13:02,420
All's good.

283
00:13:03,190 --> 00:13:04,430
Look, there's a desk here.

284
00:13:04,430 --> 00:13:05,210
Come on.

285
00:13:05,620 --> 00:13:07,030
A desk for you.

286
00:13:08,660 --> 00:13:10,620
I prepared these for you.

287
00:13:10,870 --> 00:13:12,070
It comes with a chair.

288
00:13:12,070 --> 00:13:13,120
Sit here.

289
00:13:13,270 --> 00:13:14,670
Try it out.

290
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:17,330
From now on, you'll do your homework here.

291
