00:32:32,650 --> 00:32:33,350
No...

874
00:32:33,380 --> 00:32:34,590
What are you talking about

875
00:32:34,590 --> 00:32:36,390
after listening to others?

876
00:32:36,410 --> 00:32:38,110
Have I ever lost money in business?

877
00:32:38,110 --> 00:32:39,020
Have I?

878
00:32:39,240 --> 00:32:41,000
Let's talk about this ship.

879
00:32:41,520 --> 00:32:42,880
Since I bought it,

880
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:44,050
did I lose any money?

881
00:32:44,180 --> 00:32:45,810
Haven't I been leading everyone

882
00:32:45,810 --> 00:32:47,500
on a steady path towards prosperity?

883
00:32:47,500 --> 00:32:49,700
Think about how much they profited too.

884
00:32:49,870 --> 00:32:51,800
You're worried for nothing.

885
00:32:51,970 --> 00:32:53,180
Let's decide

886
00:32:53,200 --> 00:32:55,920
after everyone has come to a consensus.

887
00:32:57,560 --> 00:33:00,480
Do you know how much it costs to drive

888
00:33:00,630 --> 00:33:02,200
a truck on the highway?

889
00:33:03,460 --> 00:33:05,210
You have to pay for the bridge.

890
00:33:05,640 --> 00:33:07,370
You have to pay for the road.

891
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:08,580
If you enter the city,

892
00:33:08,580 --> 00:33:10,020
you have to pay the parking fee.

893
00:33:10,020 --> 00:33:11,430
How much will it cost?

894
00:33:12,520 --> 00:33:14,110
These are all free

895
00:33:14,130 --> 00:33:15,560
on the canal.

896
00:33:16,320 --> 00:33:17,370
I don't understand.

897
00:33:17,370 --> 00:33:18,700
What's wrong?

898
00:33:19,250 --> 00:33:21,540
What's with the attitude?

899
00:33:33,900 --> 00:33:36,070
Have you lost some weight lately?

900
00:33:37,710 --> 00:33:38,390
No.

901
00:33:38,430 --> 00:33:40,230
You don't feel as full as before.

902
00:33:40,790 --> 00:33:42,510
I think I gained weight though. Feel it.

903
00:33:42,510 --> 00:33:44,290
Nonsense, that's your ribs.

904
00:33:44,330 --> 00:33:45,700
Where am I supposed to feel?

905
00:33:45,700 --> 00:33:46,970
Here, feel down here.

906
00:33:47,690 --> 00:33:49,010
We have to check

907
00:33:49,160 --> 00:33:50,730
your body thoroughly tonight.

908
00:33:50,730 --> 00:33:51,830
Look at my waist.

909
00:34:01,420 --> 00:34:02,590
What time is it?

910
00:34:02,620 --> 00:34:03,880
Still fooling around?

911
00:34:05,830 --> 00:34:06,550
Wanghe.

912
00:34:07,430 --> 00:34:08,830
Let me ask you something.

913
00:34:12,110 --> 00:34:13,530
How much is one jin of watermelon now?

914
00:34:13,530 --> 00:34:14,400
25 cents.

915
00:34:14,409 --> 00:34:15,139
No, 26 cents.

916
00:34:15,139 --> 00:34:16,400
It has risen recently.

917
00:34:16,750 --> 00:34:17,810
So can't our family

918
00:34:18,340 --> 00:34:19,420
afford it

919
00:34:19,449 --> 00:34:20,489
or something?

920
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:23,210
How dare you

921
00:34:23,239 --> 00:34:25,159
steal from the ship?

922
00:34:25,179 --> 00:34:26,210
Why are you hitting me?

923
00:34:26,210 --> 00:34:28,239
You stole things when you were young too.

924
00:34:28,239 --> 00:34:29,670
What did I steal?

925
00:34:29,710 --> 00:34:30,650
You stole sweet potatoes

926
00:34:30,650 --> 00:34:31,409
and chives.

927
00:34:31,440 --> 00:34:33,060
You stole whatever was in the field.

928
00:34:33,060 --> 00:34:34,100
Who told you that?

929
00:34:34,130 --> 00:34:35,639
Granny told me that!

930
00:34:39,239 --> 00:34:40,780
Why bring this up with your dad?

931
00:34:40,780 --> 00:34:42,179
You still want to...

932
00:34:42,199 --> 00:34:44,469
How dare you talk back?

933
00:34:44,510 --> 00:34:46,389
How dare you talk back?

934
00:34:46,630 --> 00:34:47,840
I'll kill you!

935
00:34:47,929 --> 00:34:48,590
Stop!

936
00:34:48,610 --> 00:34:49,360
You can't hit me.

937
00:34:49,360 --> 00:34:50,590
How dare you talk back?

938
00:34:50,590 --> 00:34:51,650
Mom!

939
00:34:51,690 --> 00:34:54,210
Mom, Wanghe is getting beaten again!

940
00:34:54,560 --> 00:34:56,230
Do you know why his father is beating him?

941
00:34:56,230 --> 00:34:57,480
He stole watermelons.

942
00:34:57,480 --> 00:34:58,480
What about you?

943
00:34:58,510 --> 00:35:00,440
You stole them too, don't you know?

944
00:35:01,280 --> 00:35:01,940
Enough.

945
00:35:01,940 --> 00:35:02,590
Listen to me.

946
00:35:02,590 --> 00:35:03,550
Enough.

947
00:35:03,620 --> 00:35:04,460
I'll beat you.

948
00:35:04,830 --> 00:35:05,710
Alright, alright.

949
00:35:05,710 --> 00:35:06,470
Why are you hiding?

950
00:35:06,470 --> 00:35:07,720
Stand still.

951
00:35:08,310 --> 00:35:09,510
In just one essay,

952
00:35:09,530 --> 00:35:10,990
you have over ten wrongly written characters.

953
00:35:10,990 --> 00:35:12,800
Your handwriting is atrocious.

954
00:35:12,810 --> 00:35:14,210
You even misused idioms.

955
00:35:14,210 --> 00:35:16,190
Are you trying to piss me off?

956
00:35:16,470 --> 00:35:18,400
Don't yell at him.

957
00:35:20,160 --> 00:35:21,770
If you feel uncomfortable,

958
00:35:22,240 --> 00:35:23,770
we can withdraw our shares.

959
00:35:23,790 --> 00:35:25,920
I'll go talk to Haihong about it, okay?

960
00:35:26,060 --> 00:35:27,120
Don't withdraw it.

961
00:35:28,640 --> 00:35:29,740
Why?

962
00:35:29,770 --> 00:35:31,580
Our pride's on the line, that's why.

963
00:35:31,580 --> 00:35:32,630
No one else is withdrawing.

964
00:35:32,630 --> 00:35:33,750
If I withdraw now,

965
00:35:33,780 --> 00:35:35,330
what will people think of me if this gets out?

966
00:35:35,330 --> 00:35:37,010
Wouldn't I look petty?

967
00:35:37,140 --> 00:35:38,100
So you know that too.

968
00:35:38,100 --> 00:35:39,420
What do I not know?

969
00:35:41,490 --> 00:35:42,610
Let me tell you.

970
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:44,520
People are social creatures.

971
00:35:44,530 --> 00:35:46,930
No other creature is more sociable than us.

972
00:35:47,590 --> 00:35:48,590
That's why even when

973
00:35:48,590 --> 00:35:49,860
an individual clearly knows

974
00:35:49,860 --> 00:35:52,060
the group is making a wrong decision,

975
00:35:52,080 --> 00:35:54,550
in order to not be isolated from the group,

976
00:35:54,590 --> 00:35:55,910
it is forced

977
00:35:55,930 --> 00:35:58,450
to follow the group's wrong decision.

978
00:35:58,470 --> 00:35:59,780
For example, the Second World War.

979
00:35:59,780 --> 00:36:00,930
So many people were

980
00:36:00,970 --> 00:36:02,730
against the war.

981
00:36:02,750 --> 00:36:04,550
But if you throw them in Germany,

982
00:36:04,620 --> 00:36:07,020
would they dare to speak up against the war?

983
00:36:07,560 --> 00:36:09,690
They would be thrown into a concentration camp!

984
00:36:09,690 --> 00:36:10,790
Let's still withdraw.

985
00:36:10,790 --> 00:36:11,920
I'll go talk to them.

986
00:36:13,030 --> 00:36:14,460
Come back.

987
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:19,190
I'll be join in this round, okay?

988
00:36:19,190 --> 00:36:20,510
I'll stop.

989
00:36:21,260 --> 00:36:22,660
It feels like someone forced you.

990
00:36:22,660 --> 00:36:23,340
No.

991
00:36:23,360 --> 00:36:24,480
No one forced me.

992
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:26,000
I did it willingly.

993
00:36:32,880 --> 00:36:34,210
What are you looking at?

994
00:36:35,310 --> 00:36:37,110
Have you reflected on yourself?

995
00:36:38,590 --> 00:36:39,800
I confess.

996
00:36:40,510 --> 00:36:41,610
This was written

997
00:36:42,160 --> 00:36:43,360
by Haikuo.

998
00:36:45,910 --> 00:36:48,450
I even bought him three sticks of ice cream.

999
00:36:48,490 --> 00:36:49,490
I kept it a secret.

1000
00:36:51,350 --> 00:36:53,500
How dare you do this?

1001
00:36:53,690 --> 00:36:55,540
Was that beating too light?

1002
00:36:56,190 --> 00:36:56,710
Help!

1003
00:36:56,710 --> 00:36:57,400
Stop!

1004
00:36:57,420 --> 00:36:58,070
Granny Ma!

1005
00:36:58,110 --> 00:36:58,870
You naughty brat!

1006
00:36:58,870 --> 00:36:59,430
Stop!

1007
00:36:59,470 --> 00:37:00,330
Help!

1008
00:37:00,900 --> 00:37:01,620
Haikuo!

1009
00:37:01,640 --> 00:37:03,150
Damn you!

1010
00:37:06,010 --> 00:37:07,870
Are you really changing the ship?

1011
00:37:10,650 --> 00:37:12,930
He said we can make more money with a bigger one.

1012
00:37:12,930 --> 00:37:13,930
Why not?

1013
00:37:14,300 --> 00:37:16,050
Is there that much demand?

1014
00:37:17,510 --> 00:37:18,650
He said yes.

1015
00:37:19,470 --> 00:37:21,310
What do you think?

1016
00:37:23,310 --> 00:37:24,470
I'm just his lackey.

1017
00:37:24,470 --> 00:37:26,150
Why should I care so much?

1018
00:37:26,730 --> 00:37:28,390
He said it, so he must be right.

1019
00:37:28,670 --> 00:37:30,740
You've worked with him for so many years.

1020
00:37:30,740 --> 00:37:32,500
Don't you know anything?

1021
00:37:32,650 --> 00:37:33,550
You're a man

1022
00:37:33,580 --> 00:37:35,210
but you have no opinion of your own.

1023
00:37:35,210 --> 00:37:36,440
What a loser.

1024
00:37:40,380 --> 00:37:42,480
Of course I have my own opinions.

1025
00:37:42,520 --> 00:37:44,030
It was my idea and opinion

1026
00:37:44,440 --> 00:37:46,040
to marry you back then.

1027
00:37:46,070 --> 00:37:46,950
So many people opposed it.

1028
00:37:46,950 --> 00:37:48,610
I didn't listen to any of them.

1029
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:50,470
Who opposed it?

1030
00:37:50,870 --> 00:37:51,730
Your mother?

1031
00:37:51,870 --> 00:37:54,000
Your third uncle, or your fourth aunt?

1032
00:37:55,710 --> 00:37:57,830
Listen, Xia Lao'er.

1033
00:37:58,660 --> 00:38:00,190
You had no house and no car.

1034
00:38:00,230 --> 00:38:01,690
It's a blessing to your family

1035
00:38:01,690 --> 00:38:02,940
that a pure maiden like me

1036
00:38:02,940 --> 00:38:04,930
married you.

1037
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:13,560
You claim you're the good fortune of our family,

1038
00:38:13,560 --> 00:38:15,220
but that's just your opinion.

1039
00:38:17,810 --> 00:38:19,150
Xia Lao'er!

1040
00:38:20,080 --> 00:38:21,210
We agreed not to fight!

1041
00:38:21,210 --> 00:38:21,970
Stop!

1042
00:38:22,100 --> 00:38:23,170
Xia Lao'er, don't run!

1043
00:38:23,170 --> 00:38:24,820
Explain yourself!

1044
00:38:25,220 --> 00:38:26,540
You always hit me!

1045
00:38:26,560 --> 00:38:28,360
I can't explain anything to you!

1046
00:38:28,390 --> 00:38:30,750
Xia Lao'er, are you really leaving?

1047
00:38:31,030 --> 00:38:32,400
Come back here!

1048
00:38:32,860 --> 00:38:34,770
Xia Lao'er, you bastard!

1049
00:38:35,930 --> 00:38:37,790
How dare you say such things!

1050
00:38:41,700 --> 00:38:43,330
What are you laughing at?

1051
00:38:43,930 --> 00:38:46,920
I'm watching the videos Haikuo took during the day.

1052
00:38:47,500 --> 00:38:48,620
It's so fun.

1053
00:38:49,650 --> 00:38:50,680
Seriously.

1054
00:38:51,100 --> 00:38:52,900
You said such off-putting words

1055
00:38:52,900 --> 00:38:54,640
in front of so many people.

1056
00:38:54,740 --> 00:38:56,410
How can Dad be happy about it?

1057
00:38:56,960 --> 00:38:58,520
It's my fault.

1058
00:38:58,920 --> 00:38:59,670
Let me tell you.

1059
00:38:59,670 --> 00:39:01,670
Dad's feelings for the canal

1060
00:39:01,700 --> 00:39:02,980
is not the same as ours.

1061
00:39:03,400 --> 00:39:05,120
We can invest

1062
00:39:05,590 --> 00:39:06,750
in that new ship.

1063
00:39:07,230 --> 00:39:09,090
It's not a big sum of money anyway.

1064
00:39:09,190 --> 00:39:10,260
It's fine if we make a loss.

1065
00:39:10,260 --> 00:39:11,700
As long as my dad is happy.

1066
00:39:11,720 --> 00:39:12,880
Make a loss?

1067
00:39:13,180 --> 00:39:14,580
Will he be okay with that?

1068
00:39:14,750 --> 00:39:15,990
Seriously.

1069
00:39:16,040 --> 00:39:17,210
All my dad

1070
00:39:17,270 --> 00:39:19,470
cares about is the prosperity of the canal.

1071
00:39:19,470 --> 00:39:20,800
He doesn't care about money.

1072
00:39:20,800 --> 00:39:22,780
Think about it. He prospered

1073
00:39:22,830 --> 00:39:23,750
and suffered before.

1074
00:39:23,750 --> 00:39:24,730
He's been through ups and downs.

1075
00:39:24,730 --> 00:39:26,950
Nothing really fazes him anymore.

1076
00:39:27,930 --> 00:39:31,620
Given that every family has to chip in for the new ship,

1077
00:39:32,320 --> 00:39:34,450
do you think Granny Ma still has money?

1078
00:39:36,630 --> 00:39:37,660
You're right.

1079
00:39:37,690 --> 00:39:39,140
She spent her all savings

1080
00:39:39,160 --> 00:39:41,090
on her son's medical bills.

1081
00:39:41,130 --> 00:39:42,600
But he still died.

1082
00:39:42,630 --> 00:39:44,360
At this age,

1083
00:39:44,380 --> 00:39:45,810
she still has to raise her granddaughter.

1084
00:39:45,810 --> 00:39:47,970
It must be hard to get by.

1085
00:40:07,630 --> 00:40:09,650
What's wrong, Siyi?

1086
00:40:09,670 --> 00:40:11,040
Can't sleep?

1087
00:40:11,950 --> 00:40:13,480
I'm thinking about things.

1088
00:40:15,040 --> 00:40:16,900
At such a young age?

1089
00:40:16,930 --> 00:40:18,530
What are you thinking about?

1090
00:40:20,750 --> 00:40:23,630
Our ancestors were Italians.

1091
00:40:23,750 --> 00:40:25,830
It was chaotic back then.

1092
00:40:25,850 --> 00:40:27,490
Why did they come to China?

1093
00:40:27,520 --> 00:40:29,570
Wasn't it better to stay at home?

1094
00:40:32,430 --> 00:40:33,110
Okay.

1095
00:40:33,550 --> 00:40:34,480
Come.

1096
00:40:34,510 --> 00:40:36,190
Come to me.

1097
00:40:36,300 --> 00:40:37,720
Let me tell you

1098
00:40:37,750 --> 00:40:40,020
about your family.

1099
00:40:41,390 --> 00:40:44,800
Your grandpa told me this story.

1100
00:40:45,380 --> 00:40:46,890
He said that

1101
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:50,100
his grandfather

1102
00:40:50,220 --> 00:40:53,180
was named Marford.

1103
00:40:53,250 --> 00:40:55,140
He was indeed an Italian.

1104
00:40:56,230 --> 00:40:57,400
During the war,

1105
00:40:57,430 --> 00:41:00,580
in order to protect his wife and children,

1106
00:41:00,620 --> 00:41:03,060
he stabbed the Japanese

1107
00:41:03,090 --> 00:41:05,810
and killed two of them.

1108
00:41:06,400 --> 00:41:07,320
But later,

1109
00:41:07,350 --> 00:41:09,360
the Japanese released hounds

1110
00:41:09,380 --> 00:41:11,250
to attack him.

1111
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:13,070
He was badly wounded.

1112
00:41:13,380 --> 00:41:15,260
Before he died,

1113
00:41:15,270 --> 00:41:16,920
he told his son

1114
00:41:17,310 --> 00:41:18,580
that

1115
00:41:18,620 --> 00:41:20,300
his brother

1116
00:41:20,670 --> 00:41:22,800
was coming from Italy to see him.

1117
00:41:23,860 --> 00:41:27,110
He was on a ship on the canal,

1118
00:41:27,340 --> 00:41:29,100
cruising northwards.

1119
00:41:30,150 --> 00:41:32,010
He asked your great-grandfather

1120
00:41:32,460 --> 00:41:34,780
to find his brother no matter what.

1121
00:41:36,130 --> 00:41:37,670
Since then,

1122
00:41:39,090 --> 00:41:42,760
your great-grandpa led the family

1123
00:41:44,420 --> 00:41:47,500
to head southwards.

1124
00:41:48,970 --> 00:41:51,410
When he reached Linqing,

1125
00:41:52,040 --> 00:41:54,390
your grandpa married me.

1126
00:41:54,950 --> 00:41:59,340
I then followed him to continue further south.

1127
00:42:00,250 --> 00:42:02,010
So we ended up here

1128
00:42:02,040 --> 00:42:04,010
at Flower Street.

1129
00:42:05,330 --> 00:42:06,570
Later,

1130
00:42:07,310 --> 00:42:11,320
our Ma family settled here on Flower Street.

1131
00:42:13,090 --> 00:42:15,070
What about the person Grandpa was looking for?

1132
00:42:15,070 --> 00:42:16,130
Have you found him?

1133
00:42:20,180 --> 00:42:22,040
It's been too many years.

1134
00:42:23,540 --> 00:42:25,000
We can't find him anymore.

1135
00:42:27,490 --> 00:42:30,280
So what if we found him?

1136
00:42:30,700 --> 00:42:32,770
That's how people are.

1137
00:42:34,220 --> 00:42:36,190
We all have feelings.

1138
00:42:37,160 --> 00:42:38,970
Just like our courtyard.

1139
00:42:39,520 --> 00:42:41,500
Look at the neighbors.

1140
00:42:42,100 --> 00:42:46,090
We respect, care for and support one another.

1141
00:42:46,250 --> 00:42:49,310
We aren't relatives, but we're closer than relatives.

1142
00:42:50,390 --> 00:42:52,490
Some blood relatives

1143
00:42:52,860 --> 00:42:55,120
don't contact each other for a long time.

1144
00:42:55,380 --> 00:42:58,250
Gradually, the relationship fades.

1145
00:42:59,780 --> 00:43:01,660
Just like my mom and I.

